<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,523,230,256]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Distribution and ecology:—</emphasis>
The species is distributed in 
<collectingCountry box="[850,963,230,256]" name="Colombia" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[975,1093,230,256]" name="Venezuela" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1106,1192,230,256]" name="Mexico" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1248,1319,230,256]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, where it is distributed from 
<collectingRegion box="[327,392,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Ceará</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion box="[432,586,266,292]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, exclusively associated with the Caatinga domain (
<bibRefCitation author="Dourado, D. A. O. &amp; Conceicao, A. S. &amp; Santos-Silva, J." box="[1168,1342,266,292]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" pagination="225 - 240" refId="ref15624" refString="Dourado, D. A. O., Conceicao, A. S. &amp; Santos-Silva, J. (2013) The genus Mimosa L. (Leguminosae: Mimosoideae) in the Serra Branca APA / Raso da Catarina, Bahia, Brazil. Biota Neotropica 13: 225 - 240. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1676 - 06032013000400020" type="journal article" year="2013">Dourado, 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Flora do Brasil" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" refId="ref15971" refString="Flora do Brasil 2020 (2020) Fabaceae. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. [http: // reflora. jbrj. gov. br / reflora / floradobrasil / FB 115]" type="url" year="2020">
Flora do 
<collectingCountry box="[136,203,302,328]" name="Brazil" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Brasil</collectingCountry>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). Souza 
<emphasis box="[365,421,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">et al.</emphasis>
(2021), found this species in Sertão region at 
<collectingRegion box="[937,1083,302,329]" country="Brazil" name="Paraiba" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Paraíba state</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,158,545]" box="[189,712,338,365]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,351,338,364]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Phenology:—</emphasis>
Registered with flowers in May.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,158,545]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,484,374,400]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Taxonomic discussion:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poiret" authorityYear="1810" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow 1806:" baseAuthorityYear="1054" box="[484,667,375,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arenosa">
<emphasis box="[484,667,375,400]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Mimosa arenosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized, mainly, by the arboreous habit, tomentose aculateate branches, inflorescence in spike and by the flat craspedium fruits. Spiciform inflorescence is a feature shares with the other 
<taxonomicName box="[201,379,446,472]" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis box="[201,291,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Mimosa</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
recorded in the study area, with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poiret" authorityYear="1810" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow 1806:" baseAuthorityYear="1054" box="[747,933,447,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arenosa">
<emphasis box="[747,933,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Mimosa arenosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poiret" authorityYear="1810" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow 1806:" baseAuthorityYear="1088" box="[988,1137,446,473]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuiflora">
M. 
<emphasis box="[1027,1137,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">tenuiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
their white flowers 
<emphasis box="[1364,1395,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">vs.</emphasis>
pink flowers on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martius ex Colla" authorityYear="1834" box="[263,428,483,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="invisa">
<emphasis box="[263,428,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Mimosa invisa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1841" box="[484,634,483,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="verrucosa">
<emphasis box="[484,634,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">M. verrucosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poiret" authorityYear="1810" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow 1806:" baseAuthorityYear="1054" box="[649,836,483,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arenosa">
<emphasis box="[649,836,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">Mimosa arenosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presents twisted aculeous and flat straight craspedium 
<emphasis box="[136,167,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">vs.</emphasis>
straighted aculeous and flat corrugate craspedium in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Poiret" authorityYear="1810" baseAuthorityName="Willdenow 1806:" baseAuthorityYear="1088" box="[765,912,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Mimosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="14" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuiflora">
<emphasis box="[765,912,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="31">M. tenuiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
